claim.claim-text:
1. A method of intercell interference mitigation, the method comprising:
receiving, at a base station, a channel quality indicator value from a subscriber station;
analyzing the channel quality indicator value;
determining, based on the channel quality indicator value, a selected resource allocation region in a communication time frame from a plurality of resource allocation regions that includes at least one coordinated downlink resource allocation region, the coordinated downlink resource allocation region comprising multiple downlink resources that are coordinated between the base station and at least one other base station for intercell interference mitigation; and
assigning the subscriber station to the selected resource allocation region.

12. A base station configured for interference mitigation; the base station comprising:
an administrative manager configured to coordinate at least one downlink resource allocation region within a communication time frame with a neighboring base station;
a subscriber station capabilities monitor configured to store capabilities of at least one subscriber station within a coverage area of the base station;
a coordinated downlink zone manager configured to determine a resource allocation region from a plurality of resource allocation regions for a subscriber station based at least in part on capabilities of the subscriber station stored in the subscriber station capabilities monitor; and
a scheduler configured to schedule information for the subscriber station in the resource allocation region.
